description:
The Third Day Before Christmas: Episode Seven is narrated by a tax collector living in Bethlehem. He tells of the census being taken by the Romans and why it is a hardship on anybody having to travel to Bethlehem to register.

A tax collector explains why his business in Bethlehem is growing, even though it comes at a high cost to those who have to be a part of the world-wide census. 

Eyewitness Bible Series is pleased to present the Christmas Series. This series is a collection of 10 new episodes designed to be watched on the three Sundays prior to Christmas week, plus the seven days of Christmas week, ending on Christmas Day.

Scripture: Luke 2:1-7
